\slide{
\cowel_html_element("h1"){\tcode{break label;}\br
and \br\tcode{continue label;}\br
\span("id"="docnum"){P3568R2}}
}

\slide{
\slideh{Introduction}
C2y now supports \tcode{break} and \tcode{continue} with a label (N3355):
\cppblock{
outer: for (int i = 0; i < N; ++i)
  for (int j = 0; j < M; ++j)
    if (/* ... */)
      break outer; // OK, break targets "outer"
}

\ul{
  \li{would be useful in C++, not just in C}
  \li{if C has it, EWG wants it}
  \li{clearly implementable, even in \tcode{constexpr}}
}
}

\slide{
\slideh{C++26 Expansion Statements}
Breaking out of loop from expanded statement:
\cppblock{
outer: for (const auto& tuple : list_of_tuples)
  template for (const auto& e : tuple)
    if (/* ... */)
      break outer;
}

Possible future direction: expand \tcode{case} labels:
\cppblock{
outer: switch (/* ... */) {
  template for (constexpr int N : cases)
    case N: visit<N>(); break outer;
}
}
}

